laboratory_examinations.findings: CT scan showed gallbladder abscess, cholistithiasis, diffuse subcutaneous tissue edema in the abdomen and pelvis, small amount of free fluid in the right paracolic gutter, small locules of free intraperitoneal gas anterior to the liver. Liver shows homogeneous attenuation with no focal lesions. Gallbladder contains gas and multiple gallstones, and a persistent cholecystoduodenal fistula is noted.
